      <heading>Wed Aug  7 (Yotsi)      :: Threads</heading>
      <slot>12</slot>
      <level>27</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>-Recent Thoughts on Thread (Multisession) RP- There are many MUs out
there, and each offers something different.  Hack'n'Slash, GodWaresque
dimensions abound, where our darker urges are channeled into fantasy,
destroying robots like the X-men in the danger room.  Fang, however,
offers the opportunity to define the depth of roleplay, with a fine and
-lengthy- set of novels as background.  Some times if I wonder if Robert
Jordan made a bet on his ability to write 10k page story.  This would
indicate something about the people on it, and their preferences in
storytelling.  -Initiating- One player submits an idea, or concept
proposal for a thread to either a Quest Imm or a (this?  ) board.  This
player is then responded to by the Quest Imm, or another authorized to run
the plot.  Any other players interested in this plot would send a
confirmation to the Thread Imm.  &quot;Blank&quot; proposals would include a brief
bit about the character's background, as well as the characters goals and
motives, and indicate an interest in being recruited by inspired Imms
looking for people to quest.  -Staging the Chapters- There would be two
kinds of chapters: - 1.  Live - An Imm is present for the RP, awarding
rolling QP at a regular interval, the quantity of which representing their
satisfaction, with something being standard.  For Chapters where the
Storyteller (ST) would like to be able to interact with the scene, or
would require NPCs.  - 2.  Logged - The interaction of the characters is
plausible, and not in a position to alter the ST's plotline.  Adding
colour and depth to character relationships and psyches.  In the middle of
Threads where the ST has left it at a pivitol or sensitive point, this may
be forbidden.  Log would be sent to ST instead of a GL, and awarded QP as
other logs.  Hopefully a player in each chapter will be willing to keep a
clean log of the Thread's chapters in .txt for reference.  -Using Mortal
Storytellers- Have Quest Imm approved proposals delegated to (or received
from) Mortal STs, who would basicly NPC and affect the scene as necessary,
sending a log in for QP as per usual.  More thoughts on this matter, will
wait for now.  Always willing to lend a limb.  ;) *Player* A.  Smith
*Troupe* -Sidhra, White RAS- -Yotsi, Tinker Fiddler- -Logos, Ogier
Scholar-
</text>
    </message>
