      <heading>Sun Aug 11 (Jasurin)    :: &amp;gRe: Yotsi&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>13</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>Ummmm, yeah.  That's sort of the idea.  The thing is, Fang has proven in
the past that it doesn't need a sophisticated administrative system for
perpetuating roleplay.  If things have changed, or if the Mud as a whole
agrees that we should really change over to a system where ongoing
roleplay is generally subject to Storyteller oversight, then so-be-it.
But right now, that's not really the Mud we are, and I personally don't
see it in our future.  This shouldn't be taken to mean that there is a
limit to &quot;thread&quot; roleplay as you call it.  The general idea, though, is
that player can produce that themselves, without anyone holding their
hands.  I, and several other Imms, are always available to assist in the
production and perpetuation of ongoing roleplay threads...  But it is my
personal belief that it shouldn't be our business to manufacture them,
or to drag them along in any particular direction.  It is the business
of each player to find and maintain their own characters' paths...  and
to come to their fellow players for assistance support and inspiration,
when they have difficulty with that.
Then again...  it may be time for a change.  I haven't exactly received
a deluge of material from people looking to advance their roleplay lately.
Comments are welcome.  Requests for assistance with ongoing roleplay,
on the other hand, are actively solicited.  C'mon you slackers, get some
plots running.

-&amp;gJasurin&amp;n
</text>
    </message>
